# Assign colors to tmux windows by group. This file is machine-specific:
# copy it to `window-colors` (same directory) and edit the groups/colors for
# this machine. `window-colors` itself is gitignored so each machine differs.
#
#   cp window-colors.sample window-colors
#
# Each group starts with a color header wrapped in brackets, using tmux style
# syntax: [fg=colourN] or [fg=colourN,bold], etc.
# List window names one per line beneath it (exact slug match, case-sensitive).
# A leading marker emoji and trailing task-indicator suffix are ignored when
# matching. Windows not listed get the default status-line color.
# Blank lines and #-comment lines are ignored.

# Work project — teal
[fg=colour6]
my-api
my-frontend

# Personal — magenta
[fg=colour13]
dotfiles
shell

# Urgent — red, bold
[fg=colour9,bold]
incident-response
